org.vngx.jsch.algorithm

Interface Algorithms


  • public interface Algorithms

    Constant algorithm names for retrieving implementations from the AlgorithmManager instance. The constant names can also be used for overriding implementations in the JSchConfig instance or SessionConfig instances.

    RFC4250 - The Secure Shell (SSH) Protocol Assigned Numbers

    Author:
    Michael Laudati
    See Also:
    AlgorithmManager, JSchConfig

      • DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP1_SHA1

        static final String DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP1_SHA1
        Algorithm name "diffie-hellman-group1-sha1" for "diffie-hellman-group1-sha1" KexAlgorithm.

        The "diffie-hellman-group1-sha1" method specifies the Diffie-Hellman key exchange with SHA-1 as HASH, and Oakley Group 2 [RFC2409] (1024-bit MODP Group). This method MUST be supported for interoperability as all of the known implementations currently support it.

        See Also:
        KexAlgorithm, Constant Field Values

      • DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP14_SHA1

        static final String DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP14_SHA1
        Algorithm name "diffie-hellman-group14-sha1" for 'diffie-hellman-group14-sha1' KexAlgorithm.

        The "diffie-hellman-group14-sha1" method specifies a Diffie-Hellman key exchange with SHA-1 as HASH and Oakley Group 14 [RFC3526] (2048-bit MODP Group), and it MUST also be supported.

        See Also:
        KexAlgorithm, Constant Field Values

      • DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP_EXCHANGE_SHA1

        static final String DIFFIE_HELLMAN_GROUP_EXCHANGE_SHA1
        Algorithm name "diffie-hellman-group-exchange-sha1" for 'diffie-hellman-group-exchange-sha1' KexAlgorithm.

        The "diffie-hellman-group-exchange-sha1" method specifies Diffie-Hellman Group and Key Exchange with SHA-1 [FIPS-180-2] as hash.

        See Also:
        KexAlgorithm, Constant Field Values
